Are you inspired by invention? Is problem solving through teamwork in your DNA? We apply advances in robotics and software to solve real-world problems that delight our customers' experiences in ways we can't even imagine yet.
 Our diverse team of engineers come from all over the world to design, test and build our dynamic fleet of robots and mechatronic systems. Having our offices, labs, test floors and factories all co-located means that we can design the hardware, write the code, test, build and watch it all come to life. This allows us to innovate quickly and on limitless ideas. Current advancements are underway in autonomous movement and mobility, artificial intelligence and machine learning, manipulation, simulation, robotic management software, predictive analytics, and much more.
 
Job Overview
 The Ops Robotics Supply Chain team is seeking a Demand Planning Manger to develop, manage, and maintain a comprehensive Sales, Inventory, and Operations Planning (SIOP) process to support the Advanced Technology group. The Ops Robotics Supply Chain Team manages a large portfolio of OEM and contract manufactured product and is responsible for supporting a wide variety of global project initiatives that cross business teams and operations groups within Amazon. This role will work closely with Ops Robotics program leadership teams and stakeholders to develop performance metrics, drive best practices, and lead process and tool improvements that align with the strategic priorities of the team.
 
Primary Responsibilities
 
 Actively support and foster a culture of inclusion. 
 Lead an integrated monthly SIOP process for Advanced Technology and other key stakeholders that contextualizes changes in the demand plan and identifies and proposes solutions for upcoming supply chain risks. 
 Collaborate with cross functional teams within Amazon and Ops Robotics to understand demand forecast drivers, including the implementation of new automated technology programs. 
 Provide input to developing demand planning strategies on existing products, new products and product phase-outs. 
 Analyze, communicate, and monitor the impacts of changes to the demand plan with Supply Chain team partners, including Deployment, Category Management, and Purchasing. 
 Support monthly inventory forecasting and reporting. 
 Track and report performance metrics and KPIs, ensuring master data is accurate and maintained. 
 Develop and maintain standard operating procedures for demand planning processes and systems. Provide recommendations for operational improvements. 
 MBA and/or Advanced Degree. 
 Experience working with Tableau analytics. 
 New Product Introduction (NPI) experience. 
 
